Marion Mack https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marion_Mack 0 Marion Mack (April 8, 1902 – May 1, 1989) was an American film actress, scriptwriter and real estate broker. Mack is best known for co-starring with Buster Keaton in the 1926 silent comedy film, The General.
